## Overview

Change the namespace container condition from `namespaces.length > 1` to `namespaces.length >= 1` so that namespace group containers always render, even in single-namespace topologies. This provides consistent visual structure and teaches users the namespace concept before they scale up.

## Files to Modify

1. `apps/client/src/layers/features/mesh/lib/build-topology-elements.ts`

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1: Change the namespace container condition

In `build-topology-elements.ts`, replace line 98:

**Current code:**
```typescript
const multiNamespace = namespaces.length > 1;
```

**New code:**
```typescript
const useGroups = namespaces.length >= 1;
```

### Step 2: Rename variable throughout function

Rename all occurrences of `multiNamespace` to `useGroups` in the function body. The variable appears at:
- Line 98 (declaration) — changed in step 1
- Line 111 (`if (multiNamespace)` — wrapping group node creation)
- Line 164 (`if (multiNamespace)` — setting parentId on agent nodes)
- Line 200-205 (cross-namespace edge source/target resolution)
- Line 220 (return statement: `useGroups: multiNamespace`)

All these become `useGroups` instead of `multiNamespace`.

### Step 3: Verify no elk-layout.ts changes needed

The `applyElkLayout` function in `elk-layout.ts` (line 34) already accepts a `useGroups: boolean` parameter. When `useGroups` is `true`, agents are nested inside group containers. The ELK compound layout handles any number of groups correctly. No changes needed.

### Step 4: Verify cross-namespace edge behavior

The cross-namespace edge logic (lines 199-218) uses `useGroups` (formerly `multiNamespace`) to decide whether to connect group nodes or fall back to agent nodes. With single namespaces, there won't be cross-namespace rules anyway, so the fallback path is never reached. The behavior is correct.

## Tests to Update

In `apps/client/src/layers/features/mesh/lib/__tests__/build-topology-elements.test.ts`, update the single namespace tests:

**Update existing test** (currently expects no groups for single namespace):

