## Overview

When relay is enabled but no external adapters exist (after filtering CCA), show a ghost "Add Adapter" placeholder node on the left side of the topology graph. This teaches users about the relay capability through progressive disclosure and provides a click-to-add entry point.

## Files to Modify

1. `apps/client/src/layers/features/mesh/lib/build-topology-elements.ts`
2. `apps/client/src/layers/features/mesh/ui/AdapterNode.tsx`
3. `apps/client/src/layers/features/mesh/ui/use-topology-handlers.ts`

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1: Add `isGhost` and `label` to AdapterNodeData

In `AdapterNode.tsx`, update the `AdapterNodeData` interface (lines 12-17):

```typescript
export interface AdapterNodeData extends Record<string, unknown> {
  adapterName: string;
  adapterType: string;
  adapterStatus: 'running' | 'stopped' | 'error';
  bindingCount: number;
  /** User-facing label to distinguish multiple instances of the same adapter type. */
  label?: string;
  /** When true, renders as a dashed-border ghost placeholder. */
  isGhost?: boolean;
  /** Click handler for ghost node — opens the adapter setup wizard. */
  onGhostClick?: () => void;
}
```

### Step 2: Add ghost rendering to AdapterNodeInner

In `AdapterNode.tsx`, add ghost rendering at the start of `AdapterNodeInner` (line 76), before the LOD band check:

```typescript
function AdapterNodeInner({ data, selected }: NodeProps) {
  const d = data as unknown as AdapterNodeData;
  const statusColor = resolveStatusColor(d.adapterStatus);
  const band = useLodBand();

  // Ghost placeholder — dashed border, click-to-add
  if (d.isGhost) {
    return (
      <div
        className="flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-dashed border-muted-foreground/30 bg-card/40 px-3 py-2 opacity-40 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70"
        style={{ width: ADAPTER_NODE_WIDTH, height: ADAPTER_NODE_HEIGHT }}
        onClick={d.onGhostClick}
        role="button"
        aria-label="Add adapter"
      >
        <Plus className="size-4 text-muted-foreground" />
        <span className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Add Adapter</span>
      </div>
    );
  }

  if (band === 'compact') {
    return <AdapterCompactPill d={d} statusColor={statusColor} selected={selected} />;
  }
  // ...rest of existing code
}
```

Add `Plus` to the lucide-react imports at line 3:
```typescript
import { MessageSquare, Webhook, Bot, Plus } from 'lucide-react';
```

Key ghost node properties:
- Dashed border (`border-dashed`) with low-contrast color (`border-muted-foreground/30`)
- Reduced opacity (40%, rising to 70% on hover via `opacity-40 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70`)
- `Plus` icon instead of platform icon
- No status dot
- No output Handle (cannot drag-to-connect from ghost)
- `role="button"` and `aria-label="Add adapter"` for accessibility
- Click handler passed via `onGhostClick` in `AdapterNodeData`

### Step 3: Create ghost node in buildTopologyElements

In `build-topology-elements.ts`, after the adapter node creation block and using the `externalAdapters` variable from Task 1.1, add the ghost node:

```typescript
// Ghost placeholder when relay is on but no external adapters exist.
if (relayEnabled && externalAdapters.length === 0) {
  nodes.push({
    id: 'ghost-adapter',
    type: 'adapter',
    position: { x: 0, y: 0 },
    data: {
      adapterName: 'Add Adapter',
      adapterType: 'ghost',
      adapterStatus: 'stopped',
      bindingCount: 0,
      isGhost: true,
    } satisfies AdapterNodeData,
  });
}
```

Note: The `onGhostClick` callback will be injected by `TopologyGraph.tsx` when it constructs the node data, similar to how agent callbacks are injected via refs. For now, the ghost node data does not include `onGhostClick` — that will be wired in the `TopologyGraph` component. A simple approach is to add an `onGhostClick` callback to the `AgentNodeCallbacks` interface (or create a new options parameter). The `TopologyGraph` component will pass a callback that triggers the `AdapterSetupWizard`.

### Step 4: Update buildTopologyElements to accept onGhostClick

Add `onGhostClick` to the callbacks parameter or as a separate parameter. The cleanest approach is to extend the existing callbacks interface:

```typescript
export interface AgentNodeCallbacks {
  onOpenSettings?: (agentId: string, projectPath: string) => void;
  onSelectAgent?: (agentId: string, projectPath: string) => void;
  onOpenChat?: (projectPath: string) => void;
  onGhostClick?: () => void;
}
```

Then in the ghost node creation:
```typescript
if (relayEnabled && externalAdapters.length === 0) {
  nodes.push({
    id: 'ghost-adapter',
    type: 'adapter',
    position: { x: 0, y: 0 },
    data: {
      adapterName: 'Add Adapter',
      adapterType: 'ghost',
      adapterStatus: 'stopped',
      bindingCount: 0,
      isGhost: true,
      onGhostClick: () => callbacks.onGhostClick?.(),
    } satisfies AdapterNodeData,
  });
}
```

### Step 5: Add ghost node connection validation

In `use-topology-handlers.ts`, update the `isValidConnection` callback (line 149) to reject connections from ghost nodes:

```typescript
const isValidConnection: IsValidConnection = useCallback(
  (connection: Edge | Connection) => {
    const sourceNode = rawNodes.find((n) => n.id === connection.source);
    const targetNode = rawNodes.find((n) => n.id === connection.target);
    // Cannot connect from ghost adapter node
    if ((sourceNode?.data as Record<string, unknown>)?.isGhost) return false;
    return sourceNode?.type === 'adapter' && targetNode?.type === 'agent';
  },
  [rawNodes],
);
```

### Step 6: Wire onGhostClick in TopologyGraph

In `TopologyGraph.tsx`, in the `TopologyGraphInner` component, add a ghost click handler that will eventually open the `AdapterSetupWizard`. For now, a simple approach: add a new optional prop `onOpenAdapterCatalog` to `TopologyGraphProps`, or directly navigate to the Relay panel.

In the `useMemo` call that builds topology elements, pass the callback:

```typescript
const onGhostClickRef = useRef<() => void>(() => undefined);
// Set this to whatever opens the adapter setup wizard

return buildTopologyElements(
  namespaces ?? [],
  accessRules ?? [],
  relayEnabled,
  adapters,
  bindings,
  bindingCountByAdapter,
  (edgeId) => handleDeleteBindingRef.current(edgeId),
  {
    onOpenSettings: (id, path) => onOpenSettingsRef.current?.(id, path),
    onSelectAgent: (id, path) => onSelectAgentRef.current?.(id, path),
    onOpenChat: (path) => onOpenChatRef.current?.(path),
    onGhostClick: () => onGhostClickRef.current(),
  },
);
```

